#: ../../making_first_map.rst:31
msgid "操作流程"
msgstr "Procedure"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:32
msgid ""
"繪製地圖的第一步，是決定我們繪製的地區。雖然我們已經知道要畫的是群島海了，但沒有詳細的經緯\\ 度是不行的。最方便取得經緯度的作法，就是去 "
"`Google Map <https://www.google.com/maps/>`_ 網站，搜尋 *Archipelago "
"Sea*，然後視窗就會移到這片海域的附近。以右鍵在你想要當作地圖邊界的\\ 區域底點一下，選「\\ *這是哪裡？*\\ "
"」，底下就會出現點選區域的名稱和經緯度。"
msgstr ""
"The first step of plotting a map is to determine where to be plotted. Even though we know we are going to plot "
"Archipelago Sea, we still can't start without a precise map extent. The most convenient way to retrieve map "
"extent in Lat/Long representation is to go to `Google Maps <https://www.google.com/maps/>`_ and search for "
"*Archipelago Sea*. When the map jumps to the region of our interest, right-click on \"*What's here?*\", "
"and the name of the region and its Lat/Long would appear in the bottom."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:39
msgid ""
"注意一下經緯度的表示法，跳出來的視窗中有兩個數字，第一個 `59.865253` 是緯度，正值表示北緯，\\ 負值表示南緯。而第二個 "
"`19.435697` 是經度，正值表示東經，負值表示西經。另外，這裡也不採用「\\ "
"度分秒」的角度格式，而是把所有零頭都歸到「度」後的小數點。這種格式比較容易進行數學運算，所以\\ 也是 GMT 預設採用的座標標示法。"
msgstr ""
"Note how longitude and latitude are represented here: there are 2 numbers in the pop-up window. The "
"first one `59.865253` is latitude; positive and negative value are N and S respectively. The second "
"one `19.435697` is longitude; positive and negative value are E and W respectively. "
"Also, it does not use the \"degrees, minutes, secounds\" convention; instead, it converts all "
"minutes and seconds and gives you a real number in degrees. It's much easier to use this format "
"in math calculation, and thus GMT adopts it as the default representation for geographical coordinates."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:44
msgid ""
"查看一番後，這裡我們選擇經度從 19.42 到 22.95，緯度從 59.71 到 60.56 的這塊區域來畫圖。\\ "
"你也可以自由選擇你喜歡的區域。接著打開\\ :ref:`終端機`，輸入如下指令："
msgstr ""
"After taking a look, we are going to select longitude from 19.42 to 22.95 degrees, and latitude from "
"59.71 to 60.56 degrees for mapping. Also, feel free to try whatever region if you would like! "
"Now, open :ref:`Terminal` and enter the following prompt:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:47
msgid "$ pscoast"
msgstr "$ pscoast"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:51
msgid ""
"會看到一連串的說明，``pscoast`` 的全部語法和選項都會列在上面。如果你對選項的意思很熟，只是\\ "
"要確認一下的話，你也可以改成這樣輸入，如此一來，就只有選項用法的部份會顯示在螢幕上。"
msgstr ""
"You would see a few pages that show all the syntax and options of ``pscoast``. If you've already been "
"super familiar with these options and just want to make sure for the usage, you can also enter "
"command like the following line, ant it will only show the syntax on screen."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:54
msgid "$ pscoast -"
msgstr "$ pscoast -"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:58
msgid "幾乎所有 GMT 的指令，包含 ``pscoast``，都是以類似如下的語法操作："
msgstr "Almost all GMT commands, including ``pscoast`` have a syntax like this:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:60
msgid "$ 指令 (輸入檔) [選項1 選項2 選項3...]"
msgstr "$ command (input_file) [option1 option2 option3...]"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:64
msgid ""
"所有以負號 (-) 開頭的文字，程式都會解讀成選項，而不是負號開頭的東西，就會是輸入檔。通常每個\\ "
"指令都會有一兩個必填的選項，而其他的選項如果沒指定的話，就會使用預設值。輸入檔和選項的先後次序，\\ 對 GMT "
"而言是沒差的，你也可以打完所有選項後，再打上輸入檔的名字。"
msgstr ""
"Every string starting with a minus sign (-) is interpreted as an **option**, "
"or more technically speaking, a **flag** or an **argument**. If a string doesn't start with a "
"minus sign, it could only be the input file(s). Every GMT command usually has a required option or two; "
"If other options are omitted, defaults settings are used. The order between options and input files don't matter "
"at all. That means, for example, it is ok to enter all options and put the name of input file in the end of line."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:68
msgid ""
"不過 ``pscoast`` 這個指令稍微特別一點點，它\\ **不用給定輸入檔**\\ ！這樣程式要怎麼知道海岸線位在哪呢？\\ 原來，GMT "
"的標準安裝內，已經有附上一個稱為 `GSHHG <https://www.soest.hawaii.edu/pwessel/gshhg/>`_ "
"的資料庫，這個資料庫內含有許多世界的基本資料，像是海岸線、國界、河流等等的位置，而 ``pscoast`` "
"做的事情，就是從這個資料庫裡面讀取資料，畫到地圖上。因此精確說來， ``pscoast`` 不僅能畫海岸線，\\ "
"也可以畫河流、國界等等的特徵。不用給定輸入檔，我們只要專心在設定參數上就行了！第一個參數當然就是\\ 地圖的座標，是透過 ``-R`` "
"(Region) 選項來設定的，選項值直接打在 ``-R`` 後方，不需要空格隔開。一般來說， ``-R`` 選項有兩種給定方法："
msgstr ""
"``pscoast`` has got a little special: **an input file is not required!** Given by that, how does the program know "
"where the coastline is? The answer is simple: there is a database called `GSHHG <https://www.soest.hawaii.edu/pwessel/gshhg/>`_ "
"along with the standard installation of GMT. The database contains a lot of basic information of the world, like "
"coastline, country borders, rivers, etc. What ``pscoast`` does is to load data from GSHHS and plot them on your map. "
"Thus, ``pscoast`` is not only capable for drawing coastline but is also used for drawing water bodies and countries. "
"When using ``pscoast``, we only need to focus on setting up options! The first required flag is ``-R`` (Region), which is used "
"to specify extent (covered area) of a map. We can just put all the parameters directly after ``-R``, without any spaces. "
"Normally, there are two ways to specify extent using ``-R`` flag:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:76
msgid ""
"-R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"-R19.42/59.71/22.95/60.56r"
msgstr ""
"-R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"-R19.42/59.71/22.95/60.56r"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:81
msgid ""
"第一種格式為 ``西邊界/東邊界/南邊界/北邊界``，也就是由 x 座標 (經度) 和 y 座標 (緯度) 的範圍\\ "
"來指定。第二種格式使用時，要在最後面加上 ``r``，這樣子四個欄位就會是 "
"``左下角經度/左下角緯度/右上角經度/右上角緯度``。以上兩行實際執行時，效果會一模一樣。這裡我們\\ "
"來採用第一種格式試試看，在命令行輸入以下指令然後執行看看："
msgstr ""
"The first format is ``W_Border/E_Border/S_Border/N_Border``; that is, we specify the region by x coordinate "
"(longitude) and y coordinate (latitude). The second format needs the coordiates of the bottom-left (BL) corner "
"and the top-right (TR) corner, so it becomes ``BL_long/BL_lat/TR_long/TR_lat``. Don't forget to add an ``r`` "
"if you are using the second way. No matter whichever way you use, it would give you the same result. "
"Here we use the first format and enter the following line in the command prompt:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:86
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify a map projection with the -J option\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify at least one of -C, -G, -S, -I, -N, "
"-Q and -W"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify a map projection with the -J option\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify at least one of -C, -G, -S, -I, -N, "
"-Q and -W"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:92
#, python-format
msgid ""
"馬上就會出現錯誤，問題出在我們還有一些選項沒有給定。對於一張地圖來說，除了邊界以外，第二重要的就是\\ 投影法了。GMT 中以 ``-J`` "
"設定投影法，有五花八門的樣式可供選擇，這裡我們來選個在畫小範圍地圖時很常用的\\ `麥卡托投影法 "
"<https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E9%BA%A5%E5%8D%A1%E6%89%98%E6%8A%95%E5%BD%B1%E6%B3%95>`_\\"
" 來看看。輸入以下指令："
msgstr ""
"Oops, an error jumps. The issue here is that we should specify other required arguments as well. "
"Except for map extent, a map projection is also very important for a map. in GMT, ``-J`` flag is "
"used for assigning map projection. There are actually various projections at your service, but here "
"we are going to pick a common one for drawing a regional map: "
"`Mercator projection <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercator_projection>`_. "
"Enter the following command:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:97
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:101
msgid ""
"在 ``-J`` 後面的 ``M`` 為麥卡托投影的代號，``6i`` 代表地圖橫向的寬度為 6 英吋 (inch)。\\ "
"如果你對英吋有多長不熟，也可以換成 ``-JM15c``，代表地圖橫向的寬度為 15 公分 (cm)，差不多\\ 就是 6 吋的長度。"
msgstr ""
"The ``M`` after the ``-J`` is the code of Mercator projection, and ``6i`` means that "
"the width of the map is 6 inches. If you don't know how long 6 inches are, just change it "
"into ``-JM15c``. This means the width of the map is 15 centimeters, which is roughly 6 inches wide."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:107
msgid ""
"``-J`` 和 ``-R`` 具有連動關係，也就是說在不同投影法之下，給定地圖邊界和尺寸的方法與參數\\ 輸入模式會有點不同，請參閱\\ "
"**GMT 官方說明**\\ 或\\ **之後的章節**。有關於各種投影法的適用情形，\\ 請參閱\\ "
"**之後的章節**\\，或地理資訊系統與測地學專書的介紹。另外，GMT 預設的大地座標系統是 `WGS84 "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System>`_ 參考橢球，如欲調整此設定，\\ "
"也請參閱\\ **之後的章節**。"
msgstr ""
"``-J`` and ``-R`` are actually related to each other. When the map projection changes, "
"the way to set map extent and size also changes a little bit. Please see **GMT official documentation** "
"or **later chapter**. For the usage of different map projections, please see **later chapter** "
"or look for it in any GIS or geodesy textbooks. In addition, the default geodetic datum of GMT is "
"`WGS84 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System>`_ reference ellipsoid. If you would like to "
"change it, plase see **later chapter** as well."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:113
msgid ""
"接下來還有一個錯誤要處理，這是有關「繪圖樣式」的設定。GMT 要求我們至少給定一種繪圖樣式，\\ 我們先使用 ``-W`` "
"以指定海岸線的畫筆屬性。畫筆具有三種屬性：粗細、顏色跟樣式，給定的語法是"
msgstr ""
"Now we still have an error left, which is about the \"drawing style\". GMT asks us to specify at least "
"one drawing style. Firstly, we use ``-W`` for the coastline pen attribute. A pen attribute contains 3"
"values: thickness, color, and style. The syntax is"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:118
msgid "-W粗細,顏色,樣式"
msgstr "-Wlinewidth,linecolor,linestyle"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:122
msgid "如果省略時，就使用預設的樣式作圖。我們試著指定指定畫筆粗細為 0.1 點 (1 點 = 1/72 英吋 = 0.03527 公分) 的黑色線條看看："
msgstr "If any is omitted, the default is used. Here we try to specify a black pen with a thickness at 0.1 "
"points (1 point = 1/72 inches = 0.03527 cm):"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:125
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:129
msgid ""
"``0.1p`` 代表的就是 0.1 點，``black`` 就是黑色，顯而易見的我們沒有指定線條樣式，程式就會以\\ "
"預設的實心線條作圖。值得一提的還有，我們在這裡使用了 GMT 預先定義的顏色名字，這些名字可以在\\ `這裡 "
"<http://gmt.soest.hawaii.edu/doc/5.1.0/gmtcolors.html#list-of-colors>`_\\"
" 查詢。"
msgstr ""
"``0.1p`` just means 0.1 points, and ``black`` tells GMT to use black pen. Obviously we didn't specify line style here, "
"so GMT will use a soild line. Note that here we used the pre-defined color name in GMT, and all "
"of these names are listed `here <http://gmt.soest.hawaii.edu/doc/5.1.0/gmtcolors.html#list-of-colors>`_."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:135
msgid "有關畫筆的進階樣式設定，例如設定線條樣式、利用 RGB 值自訂顏色等，會在「\\ :doc:`pen_and_painting`\\ 」詳加描述。"
msgstr ""
"We will learn the advanced setting for pen attribute, like setting line style or using RGB custom color, "
"in the chapeter of \":doc:`pen_and_painting`.\""

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:137
msgid "目前已經設定了三個選項，``pscoast`` 已經可以正常執行了。輸入以上指令，如果你看到類似如下畫面："
msgstr "Now we have set 3 argumets up and ``pscoast`` should be able to run smoothly. "
"Type the following command, and if you see this:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:141
#, python-format
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black\n"
"%!PS-Adobe-3.0\n"
"%%BoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%HiResBoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%Title: GMT v5.1.1 (r12968) [64-bit] Document from pscoast\n"
"%%Creator: GMT5\n"
"..... #(太長了，中略)\n"
"end\n"
"%%EOF"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black\n"
"%!PS-Adobe-3.0\n"
"%%BoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%HiResBoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%Title: GMT v5.1.1 (r12968) [64-bit] Document from pscoast\n"
"%%Creator: GMT5\n"
"..... #(it's pretty long!)\n"
"end\n"
"%%EOF"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:153
msgid ""
"那就表示地圖已經成功產生了！但嚴格來說，GMT 產生的不是地圖，而是一長串以\\ `PostScript "
"<https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/PostScript>`_ 語言描述的程式碼。我們得把這些程式碼\\ "
"另存成文字檔，然後再找個能夠解讀此種語言的軟體開啟才行。另存新檔的動作，可以透過 UNIX 系統\\ 很常見的 I/O 重導向指令，也就是 "
"``>``，來達成："
msgstr ""
"This means the map has generated successfully! Well, strictly speaking, GMT does not generate a map image but many text lines "
"written in `PostScript <https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/PostScript>`_ language. We have to save the codes as a text file, "
"and than open it using software that can interpret this language. "
"It's east to save the output as a file using a common redirecting command in UNIX systems. It is"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:158
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:162
msgid ""
"最後面的 ``> archi_sea.ps`` 是把剛才的純文字輸出轉存到 ``archi_sea.ps`` 中，``.ps`` "
"是這種檔案的常見副檔名。現在就可以用任何一種 :ref:`PostScript 看圖軟體`\\ 來打開此檔案了："
msgstr ""
"The last part ``> archi_sea.ps`` redirects the text output into ``archi_sea.ps``. ``.ps`` "
"is a common file extension for PostScript files. Now we are ready to open it using any "
":ref:`PostScript viewer`."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:167
msgid ""
"為方便閱讀，上圖已旋轉到北方朝上的角度，**實際上的出圖應該會是直向的**。不管怎麼說，這張圖看來\\ "
"幾乎完全不像目標區域的實際樣子，那是因為它只使用了最低限度的參數，尤其是海岸線的數據看起來\\ "
"太過粗糙了。現在我們要來加上一些額外的參數，讓畫出的地圖更能描述實際情況。首先先來為陸地和\\ 海洋加上顏色，使用的分別是 ``-G`` "
"(Ground) 和 ``-S`` (Sea) 選項。"
msgstr ""
"This figure has been rotated so the north is up, for increasing clarity. **The actual map output should be positioned "
"like the next figure.** Nevertheless, This figure looks pretty bad since it doesn't look like the what the targeted "
"area should be. This is because we only used the minimum required arguments. For example, the coastline data used here "
"is too crude to represent the actual shape of islands. Now we are going to add a few more flags to make it better "
"match the real world. First, let us add color for land and sea. We will need ``-G`` (Ground) and ``-S`` (Sea) "
"flags respectively."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:172
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 "
